    "summary": "The Epistle to Titus is a letter written by Paul to Titus, his coworker in ministry. Titus was left in Crete to organize the churches, appoint elders, and correct false teaching. The book emphasizes church leadership, sound doctrine, Christian behavior, and good works. Right belief should produce right living.",
    "characters": [
      "Paul - Apostle of Jesus Christ",
      "Titus - Minister in Crete",
      "Elders/Bishops - Church leaders",
      "False teachers - Deceivers to be rebuked",
      "Zenas the lawyer - Ministry helper",
      "Apollos - Preacher and teacher",
      "Artemas - Possible replacement for Titus",
      "Tychicus - Messenger and coworker"
    ],
    "themes": [
      "Sound doctrine matters",
      "Leadership must be qualified",
      "Grace teaches holy living",
      "Salvation is by mercy, not works",
      "Believers must maintain good works"
    ],
